Raise the local US 6 GHz software cap for lab-only indoor standard-power tests.

This is not a real AFC implementation. It only lifts the legacy regdb ceiling
used by this local build so the driver is not capped at the earlier 29 dBm
LPI approximation. Keep NO-OUTDOOR in place and pair this with an indoor
standard-power AP type on the hostapd side.
---
--- a/db.txt
+++ b/db.txt
@@ -2053,3 +2053,3 @@ country US: DFS-FCC
 	# 6g band
 	# https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2020/05/26/2020-11236/unlicensed-use-of-the-6ghz-band
-	(5925 - 7125 @ 320), (29), NO-OUTDOOR
+	(5925 - 7125 @ 320), (36), NO-OUTDOOR
